  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 8eb9d9fa0ccbe1b4cbcd2a1d889b806b, type: 3}
  m_Name: ThirdDayConvo01
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Dialogue
  conversationName: ThirdDayMainConversation
  lines:
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Ah, if it isn't my favorite employee! Well, my favorite <b>human</b> employee.
      Well, my <b>only</b> human employee...
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: I did have a human HVAC guy at some point, but... he uh... retired. Yeah.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: "Anyway, how are you settling in? You\u2019ve stopped flinching at the
      noises, which is always a good sign."
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: "Anyway, how are you settling in? You\u2019ve stopped flinching at the
      noises, which is always a good sign."
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: "Last night\u2019s sales were not bad! Not great, either-- but not bad.
      Let\u2019s improve on that, shall we? Tonight\u2019s <b>quota is [$quota]</b>."
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Remember, quality matters. Clean cuts, intact pieces, minimal damage--
      customers notice these things.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: "Tonight, however, I will give you a new tool that doesn\u2019t require
      cutting! Here, take this <b>syringe</b>. It\u2019s for drawing <b>blood</b>."
  repeatLine:
    speakerName: Randy
    line: Don't you have something else better to do?
